<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One way to think about it is that if you are a=
 gambling company, and it is 2020 and sports gambling is <a href=3D"https:/=
/link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32347622.263413/aHR0cHM6Ly9lbi53aWtp=
cGVkaWEub3JnL3dpa2kvSGlzdG9yeV9vZl9nYW1ibGluZ19pbl90aGVfVW5pdGVkX1N0YXRlcyN=
MZWdhbGlzYXRpb25fb2Zfc3BvcnRzX2dhbWJsaW5n/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBdfbb1483=
" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D=
"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px=
; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-colo=
r: #ccc;"> becoming broadly legal</a> in the US, you will want to market sp=
orts gambling broadly to potential customers, and the best way to do that m=
ight be to team up with a popular sports media brand. Name your sports gamb=
ling site after the sports media brand, and at the top of every article on =
the media brand=E2=80=99s website have a little call to action like =E2=80=
=9CI see you are reading about the Mets, would you like to place a wager on=
 the Mets?=E2=80=9D You are fundamentally a=C2=A0<em>gambling=C2=A0</em>com=
pany, which is still a bit suspicious and seedy to some sports fans; you wi=
ll get more customers and trust and=C2=A0goodwill from a=C2=A0<em>sports=C2=
=A0</em>company.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So, when sports gambling is becoming broadly l=
egal in the US, you strike a <em>marketing partnership=C2=A0</em>with the v=
ery biggest and best sports media brand you can get. Which will not be=C2=
=A0<em>that=C2=A0</em>big or=C2=A0<em>that=C2=A0</em>good. You=E2=80=99re n=
ot going to get ESPN. It=E2=80=99s early days for broadly accepted sports g=
ambling, it=E2=80=99s still a little edgy, and the best you will do is team=
ing up with kind of an edgy sports media brand. Barstool Sports, for instan=
ce, the bro-y and controversial site that appeals particularly to young men=
.=C2=A0And you will pay it a large amount of money for a licensing deal whe=
re you get to name your sports gambling site Barstool Sportsbook and advert=
ise it on Barstool=E2=80=99s media properties.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And you=E2=80=99ll do that for a few years, an=
d legal sports gambling will continue to take off and become more widely ac=
ceptable and normal in the US,=C2=A0and then one day you=E2=80=99ll look ar=
ound and say =E2=80=9Cwait actually now we can get ESPN.=E2=80=9D And so yo=
u will. You will=C2=A0enter a licensing deal with ESPN, where you call your=
 sports gambling site ESPN Bets and advertise it on ESPN=E2=80=99s media pr=
operties.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And it would be confusing to do both simultane=
ously, so you end your licensing deal with Barstool. And you reach an agree=
ment with Barstool not to license their name to any=C2=A0<em>other=C2=A0</e=
m>gambling sites, so that there=E2=80=99s not a Barstool Bets out there to =
confuse your customers. And you rename Barstool Sportsbook as ESPN Bets and=
 get a wider audience for your sports gambling. And if you paid Barstool $5=
50 million for roughly three years of marketing, that=C2=A0is maybe a bit h=
igh, but legal sports gambling in the US was kind of a gold rush and maybe =
that number wasn=E2=80=99t crazy.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I don=E2=80=99t know, that=E2=80=99s one inter=
pretation. The other interpretation =E2=80=94=C2=A0the one that is more lit=
erally accurate =E2=80=94=C2=A0is that Dave Portnoy sold Barstool to Penn E=
ntertainment Inc. for $550 million in 2020<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=
=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important;=
 border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-styl=
e: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; display: inli=
ne-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0and then <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click=
/32347622.263413/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMj=
MtMDgtMDgvZXNwbi1zaWducy1zcG9ydHMtYmV0dGluZy1kZWFsLXdpdGgtcGVubi1lbnRlcnRha=
W5tZW50P2NtcGlkPUJCRDA4MDkyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3Nv=
dXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDgwOSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/=
607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB5fd2d15e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"item=
scope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !im=
portant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bot=
tom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  bought it back yesterday=C2=A0=
</a><em><a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32347622.2=
63413/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDgtMDgvZ=
XNwbi1zaWducy1zcG9ydHMtYmV0dGluZy1kZWFsLXdpdGgtcGVubi1lbnRlcnRhaW5tZW50P2Nt=
cGlkPUJCRDA4MDkyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXd=
zbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDgwOSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4=
b8524a319a23cC5fd2d15e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" targ=
et=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bo=
rder-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: =
solid; background-color: #ccc;">for zero dollars</a>:</em></p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Walt Disney Co.=E2=80=99s ESPN has signed a lo=
ng-term exclusive agreement with casino operator Penn Entertainment Inc., l=
icensing its brand for sports betting and deepening the media giant=E2=80=
=99s ties to the growing online gambling business.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Penn will have the 10-year right to use the ES=
PN Bet name in the US, the company said in a statement Tuesday. Penn will r=
ebrand its Barstool sportsbook with ESPN starting this fall. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Penn also said Tuesday it=E2=80=99s selling al=
l of its Barstool Sports Inc. subsidiary to David Portnoy, who founded the =
sports and pop culture media company, in exchange for a non-compete and oth=
er agreements. Penn has the right to get half of the proceeds received by P=
ortnoy in any subsequent sale of Barstool. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Penn will make cash payments totaling $1.5 bil=
lion over the 10-year term and grant ESPN $500 million of warrants to purch=
ase Penn shares. ESPN will have the right to designate one, non-voting boar=
d observer at Penn. The casino company can extend the term for another 10 y=
ears by mutual agreement. Penn said the deal could generate between $500 mi=
llion and $1 billion in annual earnings before interest, taxes, depreciatio=
n and amortization. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Starting in 2020, Penn bought Barstool in two =
transactions totaling more than $550 million, part of the growing convergen=
ce of sports, media and gambling. The casino operator launched sportsbooks =
under the Barstool brand name and said it helped the company reach a younge=
r audience.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But the affiliation with Barstool also brought=
 unwanted attention. On an earnings call in February of last year, Penn Chi=
ef Executive Officer Jay Snowden urged investors to be patient after articl=
es on the website Insider detailed sexual misconduct claims against Portnoy=
. The accusations led gambling regulators in some states to review Penn=E2=
=80=99s business. Earlier this year, Barstool paid a $250,000 fine after re=
gulators in Ohio found it broke rules on advertising near a college campus =
and targeting customers under 21.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In a video posted Tuesday on X, formerly known=
 as Twitter, Portnoy said Barstool and Penn =E2=80=9Cunderestimated just ho=
w tough it is for myself and Barstool to operate in a regulated world.=E2=
=80=9D He suggested that Barstool had been denied state gambling licenses b=
ecause of him, and that he has no plans to sell Barstool sports again.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CFor the first time in forever, we don=
=E2=80=99t need to watch what we say, how we talk, what we do,=E2=80=9D Por=
tnoy said. =E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s back to the pirate ship.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/32347622.263413/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYnVzaW5lc3NpbnNpZGVyLmNvbS9kYXZl=
LXBvcnRub3ktYnV5cy1iYXJzdG9vbC1zcG9ydHMtYmFjay1wZW5uLW5hdGlvbmFsLTIwMjMtOA/=
607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe8b5bf23" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"item=
scope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !im=
portant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bot=
tom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">And</a>:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">"Every time we did something, it w=
as one step forward, two steps back," Portnoy said in his video announcemen=
t on Tuesday. "We got denied licenses because of me. You name it. So the re=
gulated industry probably not the best place for Barstool Sports and the ty=
pe of content we make."</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Look, as a trade, I am always going to love a =
founder selling high at the peak of the cycle=C2=A0and then buying back low=
 when valuations have collapsed. (=E2=80=9CThe Wag trade,=E2=80=9D I have <=
a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32347622.263413/aHR=
0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTktMTItMTAvdGhlLW=
RvZ3MtYXRlLXNvZnRiYW5rLXMtbW9uZXk_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDgwOTIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX=
21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwODA5JnV0bV9j=
YW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB910b7abe" itemprop=3D"Sto=
ryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; =
text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-c=
olor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  somet=
imes called it</a>, after the dog-walking startup that extracted a bunch of=
 money out of SoftBank Group Corp. when SoftBank was particularly enthused =
about, you know, throwing hundreds of millions of dollars at dog-walking st=
artups, and then bought SoftBank out cheap when that enthusiasm waned.) And=
 I suppose if this is your plan, then it helps to (1) sell high, (2) contin=
ue running your startup as a division of the buyer and (3) be=C2=A0controve=
rsial and bad at it, so the value goes down and the buyer feels forced to s=
ell. Crafty!<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"color=
: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bord=
er-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-=
color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But =E2=80=9CDave Portnoy sold Barstool high a=
t the peak of legalized sports gambling in 2020, and then bought it back lo=
w when the bubble popped in 2023,=E2=80=9D does not seem quite right? I wou=
ld not exactly say that Penn got what it paid for, with Barstool, but on th=
e other hand <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32347=
622.263413/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzkyMTczOC8w=
MDAwOTIxNzM4MjMwMDAwMTAvcGVubi0yMDIyMTIzMS5odG0jaWQ2N2U5YjAwOGZmMzQ2YWZiNjZ=
iMDQyNTM3ZDMzYmMxXzE2/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBefe39040" itemprop=3D"StoryL=
ink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; tex=
t-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-colo=
r: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Penn=E2=
=80=99s =E2=80=9Cinteractive=E2=80=9D segment</a> =E2=80=94=C2=A0consisting=
 largely though not exclusively of its =E2=80=9Conline sports betting and c=
asino app called Barstool Sportsbook and Casino=E2=80=9D and its in-casino =
Barstool-branded retail sportsbooks =E2=80=94=C2=A0went from $121 million i=
n revenue in 2020 to <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cli=
ck/32347622.263413/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzky=
MTczOC8wMDAwOTIxNzM4MjMwMDAwMTAvcGVubi0yMDIyMTIzMS5odG0jaWQ2N2U5YjAwOGZmMzQ=
2YWZiNjZiMDQyNTM3ZDMzYmMxXzc5/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1520dcc8" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
 $663 million in 2022</a>, and was <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbu=
siness.com/click/32347622.263413/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZG=
dhci9kYXRhLzkyMTczOC8wMDAwOTIxNzM4MjMwMDAwMjMvZXhoaWJpdDk5MS1xMjIwMjMuaHRt/=
607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBfe6d99c0" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"item=
scope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !im=
portant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bot=
tom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> up another 66% year-over-year</=
a> in the first half of 2023, for a run rate of almost $1 billion. =E2=80=
=9CBarstool has been a great partner and we are thankful to Dave Portnoy, E=
rika Ayers, Dan Katz and their team for helping to rapidly scale our digita=
l footprint across 16 jurisdictions in the U.S. and introducing their audie=
nce to our retail and digital products,=E2=80=9D said Penn in <a href=3D"ht=
tps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32347622.263413/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3c=
uc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzkyMTczOC8wMDAxMTA0NjU5MjMwODg4NTUvdG=
0yMzIzMDQ1ZDFfZXg5OS0xLmh0bQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8cae1f16" itemprop=3D=
"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0000=
00; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bott=
om-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> an=
nouncing yesterday=E2=80=99s deal</a>. Could Penn have added $500 million o=
f annual sports gambling revenue=C2=A0<em>without=C2=A0</em>the marketing p=
artnership? Could it have added=C2=A0<em>more</em>, without the public-rela=
tions and licensing problems that Barstool brought? Quite possibly! There r=
eally was a pretty big sports-gambling gold rush, and it does look like=C2=
=A0Penn spent lavishly and imprecisely to get in on it.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But basically Penn paid $550 million to Barsto=
ol to get into online sports gambling with a popular brand, and amortized t=
hat cost over about three years, or call it $180 million a year. And now it=
 is paying ESPN $2 billion for a 10-year licensing agreement, or $200 milli=
on a year. Portnoy didn=E2=80=99t exactly sell Barstool at the peak and buy=
 at the bottom: He sold Barstool at the point when it made sense for Penn t=
o partner with Barstool, and bought it back at the point when it made sense=
 for Penn to partner=C2=A0<em>with Disney</em>.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One assumes that Penn would have preferred to =
sell Barstool back to Portnoy for some price higher than zero, but:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">It didn=E2=80=99t make sense for them=
 to keep it,</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">It was perhaps too co=
ntroversial for most other media or gaming companies, and=C2=A0</li>=09<li =
style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Presumably any buyer would have to come to te=
rms with Portnoy for it to make sense.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So I guess Portnoy was the only bidder? I dunn=
o, I just Googled =E2=80=9CDave Portnoy enemies=E2=80=9D and got <a href=3D=
"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32347622.263413/aHR0cHM6Ly90=
d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9zdG9vbHByZXNpZGVudGUvc3RhdHVzLzE1MDI3MDE4Nzg2OTM1MzU3NDQ_bGF=
uZz1lbg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB28d9d1aa" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> this list that he tweet=
ed</a> last year beginning with Henry Blodget, and if I were Penn I would h=
ave called Blodget (a wealthy media mogul!)=C2=A0and said =E2=80=9Chey you =
can have Dave Portnoy for $10,000=E2=80=9D just to see if I could spark a b=
idding war. It is possible though that Portnoy=E2=80=99s non-compete promis=
es are worth more to Penn than a buyer would pay.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also Penn gets 50% of the proceeds if Portnoy =
sells. He =E2=80=9Chas no plans to sell Barstool Sports again,=E2=80=9D and=
 why would he? He sold it for $550 million and got it back for free; sellin=
g it again would just be greedy. Once you=E2=80=99ve cashed out $550 millio=
n and kept the business, it=C2=A0can be a lifestyle business. I assume that=
 Penn=E2=80=99s 50% is just=C2=A0schmuck insurance.<a class=3D"footnote-ind=
ex" href=3D"#footnote-3" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !im=
