<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Elsewhere in, uh, controversial founders who s=
old high and then rode their startups=C2=A0down to zero, I have always had =
kind of a soft spot for WeWork Inc.=E2=80=99s business model. WeWork did ma=
ny absurd things, which I lovingly documented, but the idea=C2=A0seems fine=
? Companies want to outsource real-estate management, lots of people work f=
or smaller startup-y companies that want flexible office arrangements, and =
particularly in this new post-pandemic world of remote work it makes sense =
for office-space management to be more flexible and outsourced and pooled. =
I feel like if WeWork didn=E2=80=99t exist and you started it now, people w=
ould say =E2=80=9Coh that makes a lot of sense.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But WeWork does exist, and=C2=A0<a href=3D"htt=
ps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32347622.263413/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cu=
Ymxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDgtMDkvd2V3b3JrLXMtc3Vic3RhbnR=
pYWwtZG91YnQtYWJvdXQtaXRzLWZ1dHVyZS1tYXJrcy1hLXN0dW5uaW5nLWZhbGw_Y21waWQ9Qk=
JEMDgwOTIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0Z=
XImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwODA5JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a31=
9a23cB99a03d3a" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_b=
lank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bot=
tom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; b=
ackground-color: #ccc;">it does not make a lot of sense</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The co-working company now says there=E2=80=99=
s =E2=80=9Csubstantial doubt=E2=80=9D it will even be able to stay in busin=
ess.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The New York-based company is bleeding cash, a=
nd customers of its office rentals are canceling their memberships in drove=
s, WeWork said in a statement Tuesday. Its shares fell 26% in the first min=
utes of trading Wednesday morning.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">WeWork=E2=80=99s stock has plunged 98% since t=
he company went public in October 2021, wiping out nearly $9 billion in mar=
ket value. The stock was trading at 16 cents early Wednesday. Its bonds are=
 also at deeply distressed levels. The company=E2=80=99s 7.875% unsecured n=
otes due in 2025 last changed hands for 33.5 cents on the dollar, according=
 to data from Trace. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">As the pandemic dragged on, WeWork insisted th=
at the shift toward remote and hybrid work would actually favor the company=
 rather than weaken its business. Employers would be more wary of signing l=
ong-term leases and would turn to WeWork=E2=80=99s flexible models instead,=
 the company argued.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Though that could still pan out, it hasn=E2=80=
=99t been happening quickly enough for WeWork. In Tuesday=E2=80=99s stateme=
nt, the company said more customers were leaving and fewer new members were=
 signing up than it had anticipated. That churn was cutting into its occupa=
ncy rate, which dropped in the second quarter compared to the previous one.=
</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Ah, well. I have also <a href=3D"https://link.=
mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32347622.263413/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZX=
JnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTktMTAtMjMvaG93LWRvLXlvdS1saWtlLXdlLW5vd=
z9jbXBpZD1CQkQwODA5MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9=
bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzA4MDkmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07c=
eef4b8524a319a23cB38a0762a" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" =
target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important=
; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-sty=
le: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> long=C2=A0been an admirer</a> of WeWor=
k founder Adam Neumann=E2=80=99s ability to=C2=A0<em>extract money from Sof=
tBank</em>,=C2=A0collecting=C2=A0hundreds of millions of dollars for himsel=
f at the peak and then walking away (for more money!) as WeWork crashed. As=
 an=C2=A0<em>entrepreneur</em>, Neumann is more impressive if the business =
he built is a lasting success, even at a lower valuation than the one he ca=
shed out at. But as a=C2=A0<em>trader</em>, his accomplishment is more impr=
essive if the business goes to zero. =E2=80=9CSoftBank made a mistake that =
involved spending $10 billion to build a $400 million company, and Adam Neu=
mann was there to take the other side of that mistake,=E2=80=9D I <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32347622.263413/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDYtMTIvdGhyZWUtYXJy=
b3dzLWhhZC1hLWZ1bi1idWJibGU_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDgwOTIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl=
1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwODA5JnV0bV9jYW1wYW=
lnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB04cb9c77" itemprop=3D"StoryLink=
" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-d=
ecoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: =
#000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> once wrote</=
a>, and that=C2=A0story is starker and sharper and more absurd if SoftBank =
spent the $10 billion on=C2=A0<em>nothing</em>.</p>
