<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Yellow Corp., the trucking company, shut down =
its operations in July and filed for bankruptcy this past weekend. Its stoc=
k is up since it shut down operations. That=E2=80=99s weird! Well, I mean, =
it=E2=80=99s <em>weird</em>, but it=E2=80=99s pretty common these days: Mem=
e-stock companies sometimes become extra meme-y when they are near, or in, =
bankruptcy, as retail investors develop conspiracy theories about short squ=
eezes and rescue deals and rush to buy the stock. And there have been some =
references to Yellow as a <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.co=
m/click/32347622.263413/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy90dXBwZXJ3YXJ=
lLXllbGxvdy1yaXRlLWFpZC1tZW1lLXN0b2Nrcy1zb2FyLWMzMWNmNTZmP3NpdGVpZD15aG9vZj=
ImcmVmPXRoZWRpZmYuY28/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc9f823b6" itemprop=3D"StoryL=
ink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; tex=
t-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-colo=
r: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">meme stock=
</a>.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But that explanation does not quite work, beca=
use a lot of the buying in the Yellow rally was done by an investment firm =
called MFN Partners that is also a big shareholder in another trucking comp=
any, and that <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/3234=
7622.263413/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzcxNjAwNi8=
wMDAxMTkzMTI1MjMxOTk4OTEvZDQ1NzcwMGRzYzEzZGEuaHRt/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB=
76a38817" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" =
style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wi=
dth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgro=
und-color: #ccc;">disclosed</a> a=C2=A0<em>42.5%=C2=A0</em>stake in Yellow =
early last week. Not really the way meme investing works. What was going on=
? I <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32347622.26341=
3/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDgtMDcva=
XJsLXMtdXNlcnMtd2VyZS1ub3QtaXJsP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA4MDkyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9t=
ZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDgwOSZ1dG1fY2F=
tcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB09ed2eee" itemprop=3D"Stor=
yLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; t=
ext-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-co=
lor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> express=
ed some puzzlement</a> earlier this week, but I suppose the simplest answer=
 would be =E2=80=9CMFN knows trucking and sees equity value here.=E2=80=9D =
<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32347622.263413/aH=
R0cHM6Ly93d3cucmV1dGVycy5jb20vYnVzaW5lc3MvYXV0b3MtdHJhbnNwb3J0YXRpb24veWVsb=
G93LWNvcnAtYXNzZXQtc2FsZS1jb3VsZC1zdXJwYXNzLTE0LWJsbi1mb3gtYnVzaW5lc3MtMjAy=
My0wOC0wOC8/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB637a66e0" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" items=
cope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorati=
on: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000=
; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Anyway</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Trucking company Yellow Corp's assets=C2=A0hav=
e attracted significant bidders and their sale could likely surpass the com=
pany's $1.4 billion in secured debt, Fox Business reported on Tuesday, citi=
ng people with direct knowledge of the matter.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That means stock holders will get a payday if =
significant unsecured debt creditors do not emerge, Fox Business reporter C=
harles Gasparino said in a post on X social media platform, formerly known =
as Twitter.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Shares of the company closed 24% higher in reg=
ular trading after the news. They fell 16% in extended trading.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I cannot stress enough that this is not invest=
ing advice and that you should not go buy Yellow stock because I said it mi=
ght get a recovery, but Charlie Gasparino said it might anyway.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You could tell a simple corporate finance stor=
y in which bankruptcy, or rumors of bankruptcy,=C2=A0<em>should=C2=A0</em>b=
e good news for a declining company. The story would go something like this=
:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Some companies are in decline; they h=
ave no good long-term prospects and will eventually stop being viable and g=
o bankrupt.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Executives=C2=A0<em>li=
ke=C2=A0</em>running their company =E2=80=94=C2=A0they get paid, they like =
their colleagues, running a company is prestigious =E2=80=94=C2=A0and are e=
ternal optimists, so they will try to avoid bankruptcy as long as possible.=
</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Avoiding bankruptcy as long as po=
ssible means spending cash on operations, losing money, gambling on redempt=
ion and not filing for bankruptcy=C2=A0until there is negative equity value=
.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Executives who are=C2=A0<em>good=
=C2=A0</em>stewards of investor capital will try to liquidate their company=
=C2=A0<em>early</em>, when the writing is on the wall rather than when all =
the value is gone. But that goes against the executives=E2=80=99 self-inter=
est and self-confidence, and so is rare.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And so=C2=A0if you see some declining company =
muddling along, you might assume =E2=80=9Cwell sure there=E2=80=99s value l=
eft here but they=E2=80=99re gonna waste it all, shareholders are never goi=
ng to see a penny of it,=E2=80=9D and you might value the stock at roughly =
zero. And then if the company said =E2=80=9Cokay never mind we=E2=80=99re g=
oing bankrupt and liquidating=E2=80=9D you might change your mind and buy t=
he stock. That is not=C2=A0<em>quite=C2=A0</em>Yellow=E2=80=99s story =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0there were labor=C2=A0troubles, etc. =E2=80=94 but it could be =
the right model. It is rare for companies to liquidate while there is still=
 value left for shareholders, but it is not impossible, and I suppose if yo=
u find one who is doing it you should bet on it.</p>
