nt; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-s=
tyle: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> the complaint</a>, which is pretty g=
oofy.=C2=A0They do not try very hard to actually make out a case for securi=
ties fraud, which requires not only that a company did a thing that you don=
=E2=80=99t like but also that it=C2=A0<em>lied=C2=A0</em>about it:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Target=E2=80=99s 2022 and 2023 Annual Proxy St=
atements, the Board assured the Plaintiff and other investors that it was m=
onitoring for social and political risks created by the ESG and DEI mandate=
s that the Board and Target management had imposed on the company. In reali=
ty, the Board, both itself and through the applicable Board committees, onl=
y acknowledged risks it perceived from failing to achieve its selfimposed E=
SG and DEI mandates. These =E2=80=9Crisks=E2=80=9D were definably not =E2=
=80=9Csocial or political=E2=80=9D risks of ESG and DEI mandates=E2=80=94ne=
ither according to Target=E2=80=99s definition nor by how=C2=A0a reasonable=
 investor would understand the phrase=E2=80=99s meaning=E2=80=94but instead=
 were =E2=80=9Crisks=E2=80=9D driven by a select group of nonprofit-organiz=
ation =E2=80=9Cstakeholders=E2=80=9D that Target worked with directly to ad=
opt those very ESG and DEI mandates. These =E2=80=9Cstakeholder=E2=80=9D-dr=
iven =E2=80=9Crisks=E2=80=9D were a pretext for Target to adopt ESG and DEI=
 mandates, not a good-faith oversight of the social and political risks of =
adopting ESG and DEI corporate policies.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Even if these =E2=80=9Cstakeholder=E2=80=9D-dr=
iven risks could be defined as =E2=80=9Csocial and political=E2=80=9D risks=
 to ESG and DEI mandates, the Board still misrepresented its oversight beca=
use the Board monitored only one side=E2=80=94i.e., whether it would face b=
acklash from having too little ESG and DEI, and not whether its divisive ES=
G and DEI mandates would create social and political risk, such as customer=
 backlash.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Sure. I guess the important point here is that=
 the stock went down. Half of Americans might think that anything a public =
company does is bad, and half might think it is good, but it=E2=80=99s only=
 securities fraud if the stock went down.</p>
